abstract: President Donald Trump said a U.S. appeals court ruling on Wednesday that a component of the Obamacare law is unconstitutional would not change the current U.S. healthcare system.
snippet: President Donald Trump said a U.S. appeals court ruling on Wednesday that a component of the Obamacare law is unconstitutional would not change the current U.S. healthcare system.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump said a U.S. appeals court ruling on Wednesday that a component of the Obamacare law is unconstitutional would not change the current U.S. healthcare system.
headline_main: Trump Says Court Decision on Obamacare Won't Change Healthcare System
headline_print_headline: Trump Says Court Decision on Obamacare Won't Change Healthcare System

abstract: Here’s what we know about if and when President Trump will be tried in the Senate.
snippet: Here’s what we know about if and when President Trump will be tried in the Senate.
lead_paragraph: Now that the House has voted to impeach President Trump, the matter would normally move to the Senate for a trial — the third for an American president.

abstract: A majority of lawmakers in the U.S. House of Representatives voted on Wednesday to impeach President Donald Trump on a charge of abusing his power by trying to pressure Ukraine to investigate a political rival.
snippet: A majority of lawmakers in the U.S. House of Representatives voted on Wednesday to impeach President Donald Trump on a charge of abusing his power by trying to pressure Ukraine to investigate a political rival.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A majority of lawmakers in the U.S. House of Representatives voted on Wednesday to impeach President Donald Trump on a charge of abusing his power by trying to pressure Ukraine to investigate a political rival.
headline_main: Majority of House Votes to Impeach Trump for Abuse of Power
headline_print_headline: Majority of House Votes to Impeach Trump for Abuse of Power

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives on Wednesday concluded a daylong debate and began voting on the first of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives on Wednesday concluded a daylong debate and began voting on the first of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump.
headline_main: House Begins Voting on Articles of Impeachment Against Trump
headline_print_headline: House Begins Voting on Articles of Impeachment Against Trump

abstract: The Democratic-led House of Representatives charged President Trump with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.

abstract: Mexican officials concerned about the health of Mexican asylum seekers including around 200 young children sleeping in the open near the U.S. border in Ciudad Juarez tried to move people to shelters on Wednesday, as temperatures dropped below freezing.
snippet: Mexican officials concerned about the health of Mexican asylum seekers including around 200 young children sleeping in the open near the U.S. border in Ciudad Juarez tried to move people to shelters on Wednesday, as temperatures dropped below free...
lead_paragraph: CIUDAD JUAREZ, Mexico — Mexican officials concerned about the health of Mexican asylum seekers including around 200 young children sleeping in the open near the U.S. border in Ciudad Juarez tried to move people to shelters on Wednesday, as temperatures dropped below freezing.
headline_main: Mexican Children Shiver in Tents at U.S. Border as Temperature Freezes
headline_print_headline: Mexican Children Shiver in Tents at U.S. Border as Temperature Freezes

abstract: From Capitol Hill to the Trump hotel to the White House, Wednesday was not a normal day, even in the not-normal Trump administration.
snippet: From Capitol Hill to the Trump hotel to the White House, Wednesday was not a normal day, even in the not-normal Trump administration.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It’s not as if anyone was expecting a normal Wednesday to materialize on Capitol Hill. Presidents don’t get impeached every day, just like they generally don’t write six-page harangues charging Democrats with “declaring open war on American Democracy”(that was Tuesday) or tweet that Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s “teeth were falling out of her mouth” (that was Sunday).

headline_main: Teaching Impeachment: 7 Ideas From Our Readers

abstract: The president traveled to Michigan, a vital electoral state, to deliver his response after he became the third president to be impeached by the House.
snippet: The president traveled to Michigan, a vital electoral state, to deliver his response after he became the third president to be impeached by the House.
lead_paragraph: BATTLE CREEK, Mich. — President Trump angrily responded to the impeachment he had long been dreading on Wednesday, lashing out at his Democratic accusers in a rambling two-hour speech and calling for their defeat in November.

abstract: The president inquired about the jet and the company’s health more broadly in a call with Dennis Muilenburg the day before Boeing paused production.
snippet: The president inquired about the jet and the company’s health more broadly in a call with Dennis Muilenburg the day before Boeing paused production.
lead_paragraph: President Trump called Boeing’s chief executive on Sunday to discuss the company’s plans to halt production of the 737 Max, according to three people with knowledge of the matter who spoke on the condition of anonymity to talk about a private call.
